                            <comment id="16761983" author="kenn" created="Wed, 6 Feb 2019 17:59:34 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Interesting catch. The code looks like it does what you expect: &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/beam/blob/master/sdks/java/core/src/main/java/org/apache/beam/sdk/schemas/Schema.java#L505&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/beam/blob/master/sdks/java/core/src/main/java/org/apache/beam/sdk/schemas/Schema.java#L505&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;But in fact this API is super confusing and I&apos;d call it a usability bug. We should just delete that static method and let the user call &lt;tt&gt;withNullable&lt;/tt&gt; on the element type. But if you delete that method and adjust your code, it looks like there&apos;s still a bug in the coder.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=reuvenlax&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;reuvenlax&quot;&gt;reuvenlax&lt;/a&gt; is a good reviewer for your PR&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16762021" author="reuvenlax" created="Wed, 6 Feb 2019 19:07:32 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;We probably have the same bug with nullable map elements. If you are planning on taking a stab, I think the correct place to fix it is in the following two functions:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;RowCoderGenerator.listCoder&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;RowCoderGenerator.mapCoder&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16762022" author="reuvenlax" created="Wed, 6 Feb 2019 19:08:27 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Also I would suggest just wrapping with NullableCoder there. IMO a bitmap would be overkill for this particular case.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
